SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 20
By Akbari
A RESOLUTION to recognize Linda Sklar on the occasion of her
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those outstanding school administrators who have devoted their careers to providing the
highest-quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Linda Sklar, who, after a distinguished career with
Memphis-Shelby County Schools (MSCS), will take her much-deserved retirement from her
position as Director of Optional Schools; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Sklar dedicated nearly five decades of service to MSCS, and she was
proud to run the optional schools and advanced academic programs for thirteen
superintendents throughout MSCS; and
WHEREAS, throughout her estimable career in education, Ms. Sklar has demonstrated
the utmost professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the unbridled respect and admiration
of the students, parents, teachers, and school board members of Memphis-Shelby County
Schools; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and commend Linda Sklar for
nearly five decades of dedicated service to Memphis-Shelby County Schools and wish her
every continued success in her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
